article_title: Falling Oil Prices Test OPEC Unity
article_text:
As global crude prices plunged earlier this month, Venezuela’s foreign minister asked to see Saudi Arabia’s top oil official at a climate-change conference on Margarita Island, off the South American coast.

Ali al-Naimi, the Saudi oil minister, was expecting a plea to reduce oil output and bolster markets. In anticipation, according to people familiar with the matter, he brought a message to Venezuelan Foreign Minister Rafael...

twitter.description: The Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries knows it must cut production to lift prices. Unclear whether its members will agree.
